    "objective": "“To establish a regression equation to properly estimate the unbound serum concentration of valproic acid (VPA) from its total serum concentration; the relationship between total and unbound serum VPA concentrations was retrospectively characterized.”",
    "covariates": "Tested: comedication Included: comedication",
    "observations": "Comedication (ZON, PHT, CBZ) are reported as having no effect on VPA CL. Ethosuximine affects relationship between total and unbound VPA concentrations, causing a decrease with comedication. A decrease in [VPA] with comedication carbamazepine, may be due to increased distribution of VPA in erythrocytes.",
    "dose": "Steady state, oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Langmuir model (relating free concentration to total concentration)",
    "equations": "Ct=Cf+Bm*(Cf/(Kd+Cf)) [monotherapy] Kd=theta1 (μg/mL) *(1+eta1) Bm= theta2 *(1+eta2) [combination (VPA w/ ZON, ETH, PHT, CPZ, CBZ, CLO)] Kd=theta3 (μg/mL) *(1+eta3) Bm= theta4 *(1+eta4) [polytherapy] Kd=theta5(μg/mL) *(1+eta5) Bm= theta6 *(1+eta6) Ct: total VPA concentration Cf: free VPA concentration",
